                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 892.001/19.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Tarler</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bangkok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-10-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 31, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 669.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that His Royal
                    Highness Prince Krom Luang Devawongse Varoprakar, His Siamese Majesty’s <pb
                        facs="0957" n="845" xml:id="pg_845"/> minister for foreign affairs, has been
                    commanded, in the name and on behalf of the Royal Family and His Majesty’s
                    Government, to tender President Taft and the American Government and people
                    their appreciation of their kind and sympathetic expression of condolence in
                    their hour of deepest sorrow for the great and irreparable loss which they have
                    sustained.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">G. Cornell Tarler.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
